<TITLE> Ribery returns as Bayern advance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERLIN, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - France midfielder Franck Ribery's return from injury provided the icing on the cake as Bayern Munich reached the last 16 of the German Cup with a 2-0 win at home to second division Nuremberg on Wednesday. Bayern, stung by a 5-2 defeat at home to Werder Bremen on Saturday, gave their fans a more enjoyable evening as an early goal from Miroslav Klose set them up for an easy win over their Bavarian rivals. Ribery, playing his first match since suffering an ankle injury at Euro 2008, came off the bench with 25 minutes to go and Bayern soon added the clinching second through Tim Borowski. Last season's double winners were joined in the last 16 by fellow heavyweights Hamburg SV, who beat Bochum 2-0, and VfB Stuttgart, who came through 2-0 against Arminia Bielefeld. VfL Wolfsburg strolled to a 7-0 win over amateurs Oberneuland but 1899 Hoffenheim, enjoying life in second place in the Bundesliga, went out 3-1 at second division Freiburg. Schalke 04, Werder Bremen and Bayer Leverkusen also progressed. Bayern, the 14-times Cup winners, eased their nerves when Klose chested down a cross from Massimo Oddo and swept a shot high past Raphael Schaefer for the lead in the seventh minute. Klose and Borowski had good chances before the return of Ribery really gave the crowd reason to cheer. His team mates responded well to the Frenchman's introduction, with Luca Toni and Andreas Ottl combining to set up Borowski for the second goa
